Well, Neil, shall we download to our memory some of the vocabulary we've learnt today?

97
00:05:05,919 --> 00:05:09,680
Streaming describes the activity of listening to or watching music,

98
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:13,759
radio or videos directly from the internet as a continuous stream.

99
00:05:13,839 --> 00:05:17,920
Something that is a commercial success is popular and makes lots of money,

100
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,920
like a new computer game or pop song.

101
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,360
A good pop song, Rob.

102
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,920
Not something annoying like Gangnam style.

103
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:27,839
Oh, well, that was a huge commercial success because it was catchy.

104
00:05:27,839 --> 00:05:31,839
A word that describes something that attracts attention and is easy to remember.

105
00:05:31,839 --> 00:05:33,360
We also mentioned a playlist.

106
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:36,319
That's a list of songs that are radio station plans to play.

107
